# FALSE POSITIVE — not a secret.
# Resembles: private-key / base64 secret rules (ssh-... + long base64 blob).
# Why benign: these are SSH PUBLIC keys (the contents of authorized_keys / *.pub).
# Public keys are meant to be shared; the corresponding PRIVATE key is what would be
# a finding. Note the "ssh-ed25519"/"ssh-rsa" prefix and absence of any BEGIN ... PRIVATE block.

